  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The LIN driver supports execution of its APIs simultaneously from all CPU cores. The user has to allocate resources of ASCLIN to CPU cores at pre-compile time using the Resource Manager module"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "LIN channels of the LIN driver can be allocated to CPU cores at pre-compile time"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "LIN channels that are not allocated to a CPU core shall be by default allocated to the master core"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "DETs are raised in case APIs are invoked with mismatch of CPU core and channel IDs."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Interrupts raised by a hardware unit must be serviced by the CPU core to which the hardware unit has been allocated to."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Architectural Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Note:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "ASCLIN is Multicore capable",
        "UART IFX is not multicore capable",
        "LIN driver from Vector not multi core capable"
      ]
    },
